articles.author: Mat Oxley
articles.title: Indonesian MotoGP:' I'd done 14 races without a mistake, so it was coming sooner or later' - Motor Sport
articles.description: Jorge Martin took the MotoGP lead on Saturday and lost it on Sunday when Pecco Bagnaia won arguably his greatest victory. A deep dive into Mandalika, plus why there’s more overtaking now
articles.content: And then he inexplicably chose the soft rear, which (surprise, surprise) didnt even last half the race. He finished half a minute behind Viñales, who inherited the lead when Martin crashed but had no… [+4506 chars]
